==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cornin
<hw>Cor"nin</hw> <pr>(k?r"n?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A bitter principle obtained from dogwood (<spn>Cornus
florida</spn>), as a white crystalline substance; -- called also
<altname>cornic acid</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An extract from
dogwood used as a febrifuge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corniplume</ent>⟦br⟧
